						<div class="postbody">Ah, I see.  Thanks for the clarification on Battletoads use of direct PCM writing (no wonder those samples sounded pretty good!).
<br />
<br />Reading the controllers twice is a pretty nice idea to avoid the DMA bug; I can see now that this wouldn't be the most obvious thing for coders to do, while trying to program the seemingly innocent DMC DMA sample playback hardware back in the 80's.</div>

